    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Okay so bid 3 to go first start your plains site. get out your ents as quickly as possible. move fast only stop at sanctuaries or if its pure suicide. You may wonder why i dont have Gandalf and i really dont need him the ents have plenty of condition removal with crack into rubble, treebeard and brooding on tommorrow. I guess corsairs could be a problem as their is no possesion removal but it will be hard for castamir to overwhelm the ents, theres only sting for the marauder and besides theirs only one dude who runs corsairs at my local tourney scene.<br />
Shadow: scout troop gets the plains site you started with. play wolves of isengard then in the regroup phase you can do even more wounds by exausting all your orcs then discarding them (and then stacking them on conditions of course)<br />
<br />
